    name: 'O\'Neill',
    sport: ['surf'],
    status: 'active',
    era: '1952-present',
    bio: 'O\'Neill was founded in 1952 by Jack O\'Neill in San Francisco — later moving to Santa Cruz — and is credited with inventing the modern wetsuit. O\'Neill\'s development of neoprene suits allowed surfers to ride in cold California water year-round, fundamentally expanding where and when surfing was possible. The brand also claims to have invented the surf leash. O\'Neill remains one of the most respected wetsuit brands in the world and a cornerstone of Northern California surf culture.',
