    type: 'brand',
    name: 'Reef',
    sport: ['surf'],
    status: 'active',
    era: '1984-present',
    bio: 'Reef was founded in 1984 by brothers Fernando and Santiago Aguerre from Mar del Plata, Argentina, who moved to San Diego to launch their surf sandal brand. Built around the iconic Reef Brazil flip-flop sandal, the brand became a staple of beach culture globally and was one of the first surf brands with South American roots to achieve worldwide distribution. Reef also became known for surfing sponsorships and the Reef Girls campaign.',
