    bio: 'Tamayo Perry was a respected Hawaiian surfer and Pipeline master who competed on the Championship Tour and earned wide respect for his technical excellence in heavy hollow waves. Born and raised on Oahu, Perry was also a professional ocean safety specialist and lifeguard. He died in June 2024 after being bitten by a shark while surfing near Ahupua\'a O\'Kahana State Park on Oahu, a tragedy that stunned the surfing community.',
