    bio: 'Flávio Padaratz is one of the most important Brazilian surfers of the early professional era, competing on the Championship Tour through the 1990s and 2000s and reaching the top five in the world rankings. Known for powerful surfing in serious conditions, Padaratz — brother of Neco Padaratz — helped establish Brazilian credibility on the world tour during a period when South American surfers were still emerging as forces in professional surfing.',
