    sport: ['surf'],
    status: 'active',
    era: '1970s-present',
    bio: 'Ericeira is a fishing village north of Lisbon, Portugal that has been designated a World Surfing Reserve — one of only a handful in the world. The town\'s coastline offers a cluster of world-class reef breaks within a short stretch of coast including Ribeira d\'Ilhas, Reef, Coxos, and Cave, giving it a concentration of quality surf matched by few places on earth. Ericeira is the spiritual home of Portuguese surfing and a major destination for European surfers.',
