    status: 'active',
    era: '1999-present',
    bio: 'Hurley was founded in 1999 by Bob Hurley in Costa Mesa, California, building on his previous work with Billabong USA. The brand quickly became known for progressive surf apparel and boardshorts and sponsored elite athletes including Rob Machado, Cory Lopez, and later John John Florence. Nike acquired Hurley in 2002 and sold it in 2019 to Bluestar Alliance, under which the brand has continued. Hurley has been title sponsor of the US Open of Surfing at Huntington Beach.',
