    bio: 'The WSL Big Wave Tour (BWT) is the competitive branch of the World Surf League dedicated to surfing the world\'s largest and heaviest waves. Unlike the Championship Tour\'s fixed schedule, BWT events are called on short notice when conditions reach the required threshold at designated venues including Jaws (Pe\'ahi) in Maui, Nazaré in Portugal, Mavericks in California, and Cloudbreak in Fiji. Events can involve both paddle surfing and tow-in surfing depending on conditions.',
    hometown: 'Santa Monica, California, USA',
