    bio: "The Zephyr Competition Skateboard Team — the Z-Boys — was formed in 1972 out of Jeff Ho's Zephyr Surfboard Productions shop in Santa Monica. Coached by Skip Engblom, the team brought an aggressive, surf-influenced style to competition at the 1975 Del Mar Nationals that shocked the established skate world. Members included Tony Alva, Stacy Peralta, Jay Adams, Shogo Kubo, Bob Biniak, Jim Muir, and Wentzle Ruml. Immortalized in Stacy Peralta's 2002 documentary Dogtown and Z-Boys.",
