    hometown: 'San Clemente, California',
    stance: 'regular',
    bio: "Ian Crane is a professional freesurfer from San Clemente, California who grew up surfing Newport Beach before moving to San Clemente at age nine. A longtime O'Neill team rider known for his explosive airs and fluid style, Crane grew up surfing with Kolohe Andino, Luke Davis, and Tanner Rozunko. He pursued the WSL Championship Tour qualifying circuit before shifting focus to freesurfing and exploration. He is a featured surfer in O'Neill's Strike Mission video series and appeared in multiple seasons of Surfline's Maps to Nowhere travel series, surfing remote breaks across Morocco, the Pacific, and beyond. In 2023 he suffered a serious Lisfranc foot injury on a trip to Morocco that required surgery and an internal brace for four months. He has since recovered and returned to freesurfing.",
