    name: 'Paige Alms',
    sport: ['surf'],
    born: 'c. 1990',
    hometown: "Haiku, Maui, Hawaii",
    bio: "Paige Alms is a professional big-wave surfer from Maui, Hawaii, recognized as the pioneer of women's big-wave competition. She grew up at Ho'okipa and learned to surf on Maui before discovering big-wave surfing in her teens. In 2016 she won the inaugural Pe'ahi Women's Challenge at Jaws — earning the first-ever WSL Women's Big Wave world title — and successfully defended it in 2017. She has won the Pe'ahi Challenge 3 times total. In 2023 she was among the first group of women to compete in the historic Eddie Aikau Big Wave Invitational at Waimea Bay, recording the highest heat total and best ride of the women. She lives minutes from Pe'ahi in Haiku and surfs Jaws on a near-daily basis during swell season.",
