    hometown: 'Saquarema, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil',
    stance: 'regular',
    bio: "João 'Chumbinho' Chianca (born August 30, 2000 in Saquarema) is a Brazilian professional surfer and one of the brightest talents of his generation. Son of Gustavo 'Chumbao' Chianca and younger brother of big-wave surfer Lucas 'Chumbo' Chianca, he debuted on the WSL Championship Tour in 2022. In 2023 he had a breakthrough season — winning the MEO Rip Curl Pro Portugal event beating Jack Robinson in the final, finishing 4th overall to qualify for the WSL Finals, and securing Brazil's 2024 Olympic quota. He is the first Brazilian to top the WSL World Ranking who has not won a world title. He competed at the 2024 Paris Olympics at Teahupo'o, winning Brazil's silver medal. A Volcom-sponsored surfer, he comes from one of the most accomplished surfing families in Brazil.",
