    sport: ['surf'],
    location: 'Daytona Beach / Ormond Beach, FL (Volusia County)',
    era: '1930s–1990s',
    bio: "Gaulden Reed is the original Volusia County surf pioneer — a waterman who was riding waves in the Daytona Beach / Ormond Beach area beginning in the 1930s, decades before surfing became a mainstream pursuit on the East Coast. He wintered in Hawaii, absorbing the roots of the sport from its source. He built the Ormond Beach Pier and authored a memoir titled Once Upon a Wave. Reed was inducted into the East Coast Surfing Hall of Fame in 1998, recognizing his foundational role in establishing surf culture along the Volusia County coastline.",
