    bio: "A Cool Wave of Color (1964) is a surf film directed by Greg Noll, the legendary big-wave pioneer and shaper from Hermosa Beach known as 'Da Bull.' The film documents the early big-wave surfing culture at Waimea Bay and across the Pacific.",
