    role: 'Surf Film (Fiction)',
    bio: "Big Wednesday (1978) is a fiction surf film directed by John Milius, widely regarded as one of the greatest surf films ever made despite being a narrative drama rather than a documentary. It follows three California surfers from the 1960s through the Vietnam era into the 1970s. The surfing sequences — featuring Jan Thielbahr, Peter Townend, and Ian Cairns as surf doubles — are considered among the finest ever filmed. It has achieved cult classic status among surfers worldwide.",
