    sport: ['surf'],
    role: 'Surf Documentary',
    bio: "Andy Irons: Kissed by God (2018) is a documentary film exploring the life, competitive career, and personal struggles of three-time world champion Andy Irons. The film unflinchingly examines his battle with bipolar disorder and addiction — particularly opioids — and his death in November 2010. Directed by Todd Tune and Steve Jones, it features interviews with Kelly Slater, Rob Machado, Bruce Irons, and Lyndie Irons. The film won widespread praise for its honesty and became a landmark in action sports storytelling.",
