    sport: ['surf'],
    location: 'Malibu, CA',
    era: '1950s',
    bio: "Kathy Kohner is the real-life surfer who inspired the Gidget phenomenon. As a teenager in the late 1950s she surfed Malibu with the local Malibu crew — including Mickey Dora and Terry 'Tubesteak' Tracy — who nicknamed her 'Gidget' (Girl + Midget). Her father Frederick Kohner wrote the novel Gidget (1957) based on her stories, which became the 1959 film. The Gidget franchise — films, TV series, and cultural permeation — sparked the first mainstream American surfing craze.",
