    bio: "Matt Warshaw is the preeminent surf historian and author of the Encyclopedia of Surfing (EOS) — the most comprehensive archive of surf history ever assembled. A former competitive surfer who appeared on the WCT in the 1980s, he transitioned to journalism and history, writing for Surfer Magazine before publishing The Encyclopedia of Surfing (2003) and its subscription-based digital version at eos.surf. His other books include The History of Surfing (2010). He is the definitive authority on surf history.",
