    sport: ['wakeboard'],
    bio: "Meagan Ethell is an American professional wakeboarder from Channahon, Illinois, born in 1997. She began wakeboarding at eight and made it her sole focus at 12. An advocate for gender equality in wake sports, she is the face of the Moxie Pro — the first women's-only wakeboard contest. She won the WWA Worlds in 2020 and is a consistent podium finisher worldwide.",
