    name: "Aaron Hadlow",
    sport: ['kitesurf'],
    bio: "Aaron Hadlow is a British professional kiteboarder born October 4, 1988, and one of the most decorated riders in the sport's history. He won the PKRA World Championship five consecutive times from 2004 to 2008 — the only rider to achieve this. He won the Red Bull King of the Air in 2015 and 2016, became known for innovations that competitors were only dreaming of, and co-founded his own kite brand HADLOW by Flexifoil. In 2024 he remains involved in kite research and development.",
