    bio: "Adam Ondra is a Czech professional rock climber born February 5, 1993, and broadly regarded as the greatest rock climber of all time. He was the first to climb 9c (Silence, 2017) — still the world's hardest rated route. He has freed multiple previously unclimbed big wall routes in Yosemite and holds numerous World Championship and World Cup titles. He is a Red Bull athlete whose documentary Change climbed to wide acclaim.",
