    sport: ['base', 'skydive', 'wingsuit'],
    bio: "Felix Baumgartner is an Austrian skydiver, BASE jumper, and extreme athlete born April 20, 1969, in Salzburg. He is best known for the Red Bull Stratos mission on October 14, 2012, in which he jumped from the edge of space (128,100 feet / 39km) and became the first human to break the sound barrier in freefall, reaching 1,357 km/h (Mach 1.25). He also set the record for highest ever parachute jump. Baumgartner performed the first BASE jump across the English Channel (2003) and from the Christ the Redeemer statue in Rio de Janeiro. He retired from competitive jumping after Red Bull Stratos.",
